    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="http://wellfed.typepad.com/" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Grant</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2007/01/a-bad-case/#comment-6897"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2007-01-10T01:13:00-05:00">Wednesday, January 10, 2007 at 1:13 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I&#8217;m so into pureed soups recently.  And I love the idea of one made from a celery root.  I encountered a similar supermarket checker when I was home for Thanksgiving and needed a celery root for the stuffing I was making.  Eyes narrowed and nose scrunched as she sneered &#8220;What IS that?&#8221;</></>I&#8217;m wanting to do more with celery roots now.  When I was in England I had an amazing tart that was filled with shredded celery root, leeks and Godminster cheese.  I feel like you would have loved it.</p>
