    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I guess we&#8217;re just old-fashioned here in Holland, because most of these veggies are standard winter fare. Celery root is part of our classic split pea soup (with leek &#038; potato too) and kale is usually chopped &#038; boiled, then mixed with mashed potatoes (works for most greens) and serves with sausage or cheese if you&#8217;re veg.</p>
