  <li id="comment-6958" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/08796398094244456423" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Drew</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2007/01/a-bad-case/#comment-6958"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2011-04-26T23:50:50-04:00">Tuesday, April 26, 2011 at 11:50 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Just tried this for the first time the other day, inspired by this post and an article about root vegetables in the last food issue of the New Yorker&#8212;it was great! Will definitely be making again. Loved the smell of the celery root when dicing it&#8230;filled up the whole house.</p>
    </div>

      </li><!-- #comment-## -->
  <li id="comment-6959" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/16170386582612018304" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Yelli</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2007/01/a-bad-case/#comment-6959"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2012-02-02T03:11:35-05:00">Thursday, February 2, 2012 at 3:11 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>My whole family was blown away by this soup. My 5YO and 1YO both had seconds leaving no seconds for the DH and I. 🙁 </p>
<p>I didn&#39;t have enough celery root so I add one baked potato at the end and we also added chopped parsley instead of chervil. This was marvelous. The color was gorgeous and the texture was wonderful. I would also add that using a hand blender made it extremely easy to blend in the pot instead of blender/food processor. </p>
<p>Another recipe hit that the whole family enjoyed!!!!</p>
    </div>

      </li><!-- #comment-## -->
  <li id="comment-6960" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/16170386582612018304" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Yelli</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2007/01/a-bad-case/#comment-6960"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2012-02-02T03:11:35-05:00">Thursday, February 2, 2012 at 3:11 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>My whole family was blown away by this soup. My 5YO and 1YO both had seconds leaving no seconds for the DH and I. 🙁 </p>
<p>I didn&#39;t have enough celery root so I add one baked potato at the end and we also added chopped parsley instead of chervil. This was marvelous. The color was gorgeous and the texture was wonderful. I would also add that using a hand blender made it extremely easy to blend in the pot instead of blender/food processor. </p>
<p>Another recipe hit that the whole family enjoyed!!!!</p>
    </div>

